

=Description=

"Career Pivoting – More “controlled” career path revisions seem to be occurring more and more often – sometimes out of the need to stay where the work is and in other cases to pursue a better career fit.  As a result, pivoting has become much more common. Pivoting often entails a change in specific work setting or industry – but many components of the current skill set are applied to a new role.  How these adjustments will be a focus – and vehicles such as mid-career internships may become more popular (and important).  How many are choosing a pivot, instead of a more drastic career change? How plentiful are the opportunities for a career pivot? Are internships there for those who want or need a mid-career revision?"
(http://marlagottschalk.wordpress.com/2011/09/18/the-evolution-of-work-as-we-know-it/)


